LOLCAT(6)                               Games Manual                              LOLCAT(6)

NNAAMMEE
       lolcat - rainbow coloring effect for text console display

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
       lloollccaatt [_o_p_t_i_o_n_s] [_f_i_l_e_s] ...

DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       This manual page documents briefly the lloollccaatt command.

       lloollccaatt  is  a program that concatenates files, or standard input, to standard output
       (like the generic ccaatt), and adds rainbow coloring to it.

OOPPTTIIOONNSS
       --pp _X, ----sspprreeaadd==_X
              Inclination of the rainbow stripes
              (character widths per line hight; high values (>1000) give  almost  horizonal
              stripes, low values (0.1) almost vertical ones; default: 3.0).

       --FF _X, ----ffrreeqq==_X
              Frequency of the rainbow effect.
              (low values around 0.0001 give almost monochromous screens; default: 0.1).

       --SS _X, ----sseeeedd==_X
              Initial value for the random number generator; 0 means automatic.
              (default: 0).

       --aa, ----aanniimmaattee
              Fade every line through an animation before printing the next one.

       --dd _X, ----dduurraattiioonn==_X
              Duration of the animation.
              (number of steps before showing next line; default: 12)

       --ss _X, ----ssppeeeedd==_X
              Speed of the animation.
              (frame rate, ie. number of steps per second; default: 20)

       --ii, ----iinnvveerrtt
              Inverts the background and foreground colors.

       --tt, ----ttrruueeccoolloorr
              Enables 24-bit truecolor mode.

       --ff, ----ffoorrccee
              Force color even when stdout is not a tty.

       --vv,, ----vveerrssiioonn
              Shows lolcat version.

       --hh,, ----hheellpp
              Shows options summary.

EEXXAAMMPPLLEESS
       Typical combinations of lloollccaatt include other programs that generate text:
       Large colorful words can be written like this:

              echo "KTHXBAI" | toilet | lolcat

       Cows are popular, come in all colors, and tell random epigrams:

              fortune | cowsay | lolcat -a

SSEEEE AALLSSOO
       ccaatt(1), ttooiilleett(1), ffoorrttuunnee(6), ccoowwssaayy(6)

